  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "We briefly summarise the approach of time-delay cosmography in Sect. 2.1, and focus on SNe as lensed background sources, which are \"standardisable candles\" and a relative distance indicator.",
    "In Sect. 2.2, we describe approaches to measure time delays of lensed SNe, particularly novel ones through spectroscopic observations of SNe, which complement conventional techniques using photometric light curves.",
    "In Sect. 2.3, we show the present cosmological constraints and future forecasts from lensed SNe.",
    "We describe the various distance measurements that we can obtain from strongly lensed SNe, through the lensing time delays and the SN light curves.",
    "We briefly summarise the determination of the lensing distances that are covered in detail in the parallel reviews by, e.g., Birrer et al. (2024), and focus particularly on the new aspects that SNe bring."
  ],
